Nigerian nationals living in South Africa have commended President Muhammadu Buhari over completion of the Abuja light rail project, which was commissioned yesterday. The President of Nigeria Union in South Africa (NUSA), Mr Adetola Olubajo, in a statement made available to newsmen, said the project would ease traffic congestions in the capital city. “We celebrate the President for his commitment to improve infrastructural facilities regardless of numerous challenges facing our country now,” he said.